                     <p>
                        <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Thozmotby</surname>
                        </persName>,
                  son and heir of the late <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de<surname>Thormotby</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                  confirms to <persName>
                           <forename>Margaret</forename>, daughter of <persName>
                              <forename>John</forename> de
                  <surname>Kyrkeby</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, for a sum of money paid to the heirs, one toft and croft 
                  in the village of <placeName key="place_103240">Kyrkeby</placeName> which is called <placeName type="minor">Bulloko</placeName> toft; 
                  to hold for 30 years from Monday before ... <origDate when="1304">1304</origDate>, 
                  and after 30 years to be held for a yearly rent of 5s. 
                  Defaced.
                  . </p>
